European inflation slipped in food
Inflation accelerated, recorded in the euro zone, is due firstly to the rapid growth in the price of food products.
The rise in prices in the month of November has been higher than expected in the 13 countries of the euro zone, recording - after 2.6% in October - an annual inflation of 3.1% - announced the statistical office of the Union based in Luxembourg.
The official forecasts were just as likely a 3% - announced the Bloomberg.
The European Central Bank (ECB), in contrast to the issuing banks American, British and Canadian, not cut the basic interest, on the pretext that the reduction, together with rising prices of raw materials, and forced to reduce unemployment, would lead to a spiral of inflation.
The ECB wants to keep the inflation rate below, but at least close to 2%.
According to one analyst, the ECB is in the trap 22: "We must negotiate" on inflation so that subsequently does not have to intervene in this issue.
Inflation of 3.3%, registered in Germany, beating the record of twelve years; whereas in Espana increased from 3.6 to 4.1%.
Inflation were shot in the euro zone as a result of the rampant food prices and energy.
Contributions term of wheat increased by 88% and also the price of soya reached its highest level since 1973.
Similarly, there were to pay much more in 2007 for the vegetable oil and dairy products.
The price of crude oil in the world market increased this in a 52%, reaching already last month the black gold nearly 100 dollars a barrel.
According to the ECB, inflation in 2008 2.1% now to 2.5%, in exchange for the 2009 will fall to 1.9.
According to analysts, the annual inflation will remain in the next 3 or 4 months around 3%, but the annual average rate will be 2.1%.
At the same time, it is expected that during the 2008 the ECB to reduce interest rates twice.
Gallup provides for a government crisis
After a long stagnation, at the beginning of December the support of the Alliance of young Democrats rose significantly, reaching its highest level since 2002, while the Gallup never before experienced such a low level - a 13% - in the case of the Socialists.
The difference in the case of the electorate sure of the parties, due to the greater strength of voters in the opposition - would mean a support of more than two-thirds (71%) in the face of the support of a fifth for the Socialists (20%).
According to the survey, the democratic forum and the alliance of free Democrats nor the limit necessary to take some Escano: its parliamentary support within the entire population is 2%.
Among voters insurance there is more than one per cent supporters on both sides.
The economic environment continued to deteriorate even in comparison with the previous lowest point - has never been so high, 41% the proportion of those who judged particularly bad the economic situation in the country, while another 46% believes that the situation is rather bad.
The families, after expectations more hopeful of the spring and the summer, are now more pessimistic about the change of their own economic situation.
With regard to the next, the majority of the population has the deterioration of the situation and only a tenth expected to improve.
In December, 71% of those questioned, a figure higher than any previous survey Gallup, estimated that the head of government Desempena more harm than good.
13% of consulted trusts or Ferenc Gyurcsány, while Viktor Orbán has the support of 38 percent of consulted.
A 54% of the population does not trust it all in the head of government and a 27% does not trust the President of the Alliance of young Democrats.
One of the indicators of the shape of the political situation is that, what proportion of the society thinks that it is possible to monitor the discontent experienced in the face of the person of the head of government without a change of government.
While after the riots in October last 35% believed that it would be desirable to maintain in power the government and the head of government, currently this proportion is only 20%, while the relative majority (33%) believes that the only solution is new elections.
The interest in the referendum is characterised by the fact that 60% of respondents to the question on the participation replied that surely would participate and another 20% said that it is likely to be involved.
As a comparison, in "a general election to be held this Sunday" participate with security only 55% of the population and another 15% think likely their participation. On the basis of the current intentions of the voters there can be no doubt of the outcome of the referendum.
74% of the population paying the rights of studies, 79% of the service of medical consultations and a 84% of hospital care.
If we look at these proportions only between the participants insurance in the referendum, 81, 84 and 89% of the electorate would reject the introduction of the rights of studies, the payment for the medical consultations and of the care hospital.
The most expensive is the Auchan, the Tesco their prices
held the average increase of the level of prices of 16% supermarkets of the triangle commercial gold Budaörs, with the difference that this has not been an increase in the VAT.
Article by Napi Gazdaság
This also rose by an average of 16% in the triangle trade gold Budaörs the Canasta usual Christmas Journal Napi, but in all supermarkets recorded a growth much higher than the thousand Huf.
As in December last had already been "fired" prices of food in supermarkets, this is not experienced a drastic increase percentage compared to the high starting point.
However, it is obviously terrifying for consumers the fact that what the past were able to buy at a price far below the nine thousand Huf today can not do or ten thousand.
The Canasta of Napi in supermarkets studied exceeded with a minimum of 91 Huf the psychological limit of ten thousand Huf.
And the Canasta of highest value was 10 573 Huf.
(in the 2003 that Canasta cost 6800 Huf.)
The price of spirits and fish remained almost at the level of the previous one, but there was a sharp increase in the steak of Pechuga of Turkey, nut and seed poppy.
The price of wheat flour and bread followed the data of the Central Bureau of Statistics, although in the Auchan we have found a kilo of bread for the price of 139 Huf.
Competition does not cut the price of the product to less than 200 Huf.
Equally surprising was in this shop that the price of Coca-Cola bottle with Redimible of two litres cost less than 200 Huf, so this product, even with the price of the bottle, cost only 257 Huf.
However, in the Canasta of Napi Auchan was the most expensive, while Cora the cheapest.
According to our calculations, with regard to the prices of the Christmas of the past, Cora increased with 15, while Tesco and Auchan with around 18% prices in the Canasta of Napi.
Comparing the values of Canasta more expensive of the past with that of the cheapest Canasta of this, the difference has been a 12%, while growth between the cheapest of the past and the most expensive of this has been a 21%.
The average growth was 1480 Huf.
The past the average growth in prices was of 1206 Huf, so that during the Christmas of the past in prices was the increase in VAT.
It is precisely this process which was destroyed trade, supermarkets visibly were unable to take a decision on the room for prices to apply for each product and to calculate the effect of the change of prices on consumption.
(if the trader planning badly the speed of the movement of a product, stands to lose an important benefit in the margin which is in line with sales figures.)
The increase in the price of the Canasta of Napi reached such extremes as a result of the increase in the VAT, which is the most expensive was higher with 1720 Huf to the value recorded in 2006, while in the cheaper The difference was just a Huf.
This not there were such extremes, given that the highest price of now has been 1630 Huf more than the past and the cheapest also increased with 1284 Huf.
Comparing the two seasons Navidenas, there was a catastrophic growth in prices in less than 20 months, in supermarkets grew more than 30% the price of consumer articles basic necessities.
(But this does not necessarily confirms the figures of the Central Bureau of Statistics: this office, in the case of some basic foodstuffs recorded in the interval of 12 months an increase in price of over 30%.
For example, in addition to the wheat, also in the case of the chicken.)
According to the Canasta of Napi, in the latter case that seems almost impossible, because the price of this product that was quite expensive because the past compared to the basis, there was, in the worst case, only a 10% increase in prices.
According to all the indicators, suppliers of meal have a stronger position than those of egg, and could impose the dramatic increase in prices even the multinationals.
Supermarkets not complain in the triangle trade of gold, talk constantly about positive results.
According to our experience, the majority of consumers of the three shops visited, already are not interested in prices.
Of all the products they buy large quantities, and by Paletas food preserved.
In the Manana on Wednesday, in the three shops are formed huge queues ahead of the boxes because suddenly increased the number of customers.
However, we have information that in the interior of the country the volume of sales are lower, many multinationals complain institutes survey because incomes are below their plans, and not just in the case of food, but also for the household appliances.
In many hospitals saves with disinfectants
This has been made in hospitals several thousand infections produced in the first place over their misuse of antibiotics.
The circumstances of hygiene prevailing in hospitals, overcrowding of beds and pollution staff not encourage the control of infection - says the Médica-jefa unit of the national centre for epidemiology.
In many hospitals saves even with the disinfectants.
Not long ago has been diagnosed an infection with MRSA in the department of Traumatología the hospital János.
In a man in hospital after a serious accident was detected the presence of bacteria resistant to antibiotics.
The patient was isolated.
The same type of infection occurred in the same hospital at the beginning of the Minister.
A wounded a serious car accident gave high of the hospital and the same patient shortly after due to return to the hospital as a result of infection with MRSA and since then we have not been able to make an important surgical intervention by the presence of bacteria in his body.
Until 10 December this has been made in the national system Nosocomialis surveillance 1094 cases of infection hospital produced by agents - said Karolina Böröcz, Médica-jefa unit of the national centre for epidemiology.
This means that in hospitals certainly there has been this number of infections caused by agents, of the rest do not have the information.
Nearly two-thirds of the infections (683 cases) are due to MRSA, staphylococcus aureus resistant to the Meticilina-oxacilina.
A third of human beings have been in its nose of bacteria staphylococcus aureus (SA) without causing disease.
Infections caused by the SA (for example: inflammation of the throat, Amigdalitis, skin infections, infections of wounds) are reacting well to antibiotics and are easily treatment.
However, once implemented exaggerated or unduly antibiotics, bacteria that normally react well to antibiotics, it becomes very bacteria resistant to antibiotics and quickly in a position hospital inadequate.
Can cause serious infections, for example hospital infections of wounds firstly patients with immune deficiency transitional or chronic, patients with weakened the body, the elderly or people of little weight.
In view of the Médico-director the hospital János there is nothing special in the infection MRSA, these infections are daily in hospitals.
The infection should not be confused with the epidemic, the only MRSA is absent - said Tibor Nyulasi - where there is examined its presence.
Which is resistant to antibiotics
"these patients are isolated, nursing staff in Goma gloves and mask and there are suited to antibiotics treatment" - said Tibor Nyulasi.
Patients hospitalized are being examined prior to verify the presence of the MRSA in his body, but not even in this way can we avoid the infection in all cases.
It is fashionable not take samples
It would be possible to prevent hospital infections of the MRSA in most cases, but the current circumstances hospital not encourage national training and for the prevention of infection with the pathogens - says Karolina Böröcz.
As this infection occurs mainly in hospitals and homes for the elderly, hospitals should examine patients hospitalized and isolate immediately Enfermes in his body the MRSA.
However, in hospitals Hungarians is not fashionable the microbiological sampling.
This is also due to the box national health not financed these medical examinations.
So the majority of cases come to light public when there are already infections of the MRSA visible in the patient - said the Médica-jefa of department of central epidemiological.
The European Union is rigorous Encomiendas for the implementation of antibiotics in human medicine and there are also directives to deal with the national infections and tables disease.
We must Empenarse that therapy with antibiotic be addressed, that is, should be done microbiological tests to prevent resistance to medicines, but hospitals do not always meet this requirement.
The sampling microbiological are even less frequent in the case of patients or assistance basic - said Karolina Böröcz.
SAVE with the disinfectants
scientific experiments have shown that in most cases the MRSA infect a patient to another through medical staff.
Therefore, a very important role Desempenan laundering of hand, the use of rubber gloves and masks, but also in this regard are experiencing considerable errors in hospitals.
The MRSA through the transmission by drops and the direct contact between people, but in the circumstances national hospital is not always possible to isolate the patient infected.
What is more, the rooms hospitals are often overcrowded, beds are often very together, but to prevent the epidemic, patients should be separated by at least a distance of 1.5 metres.
Unfortunately may have also added - Karolina Böröcz - that in hospitals of less favourable economic situation saves with disinfectants, there are few nurses and many patients and that is why there is a greater likelihood for the infection.
In view of Karolina Böröcz, where they meet the appropriate measures of prevention, there are less infections such or can halt the spread of the pathogen.
Programme governmental against MRSA
The treatment of infection with MRSA is a huge expenditure for the fund national health insurance, so that in all countries fight against him.
In Britain, for example, there is a government programme to prevent and reduce the cases of the MRSA.
It appears that the programme has successes, according to the data provided, infection with MRSA show trend of reduction in England.
The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) has on its agenda the prevention of actors (among these the MRSA) and that of the hospital infections are due to these pathogens.
Negative alcohol control of the commander of police who caused a fatal accident
The report has been made official expert on the case of the fatal accident caused by the commander of the police district XXII.
We can exclude the possibility that led or state overwhelmed the Since then resigned commander of the police district XXII, who on Tuesday and caused the death of a passer-by - reported on Friday Attila Morvai, spokesman for the public prosecutor of the capital, after having prepared the expert report on the case.
The expert report confirmed the result of the primary control of alcohol that had already established that the former Commander of the police not consumed alcoholic beverage before they get behind the wheel.
Then the head of the police station of the police district XXII, on Tuesday with his vehicle particular double to the streets Kossuth Lajos district XXII a man of 55, who intended to cross the street, but not in the area designated for pedestrians.
(The latter fact, namely that the pedestrian not used to cross the street, according to the regulations of the code of transit are not extenuating circumstances, the driver must always give way before the double.)
The lost his life after being in hospital.
The leader for what happened police district resigned and called for their retirement, according to the communiqué of the police, because I moved much the case.
The investigation of the case is in charge of the public prosecutor's office of research in Budapest.
Attila Morvai said that the former Commander of the police from the outset worked with prosecutors charged with the research.
400 million more for infrastructure
The Hungarian Minister of Finance János Veres and the Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB) Marta Gajecka signed on Friday in Budapest three Acuerdos-limite credit for a total value of 400 million to finance infrastructure of education, transport and the environment, as well as in the energy sector.
The European Investment Bank (EIB) adopted in 2006 a budget of EUR 300 million to projects of transport and environmental protection of the funding of the Cohesion Fund, which parties already had signed a contract of credit to the value of 100 million, the contract has just been signed it concerns the use of the remaining EUR 200 million.
The contract credit of 150 million to finance the budget of educational projects.
The EIB approved a total of EUR 300 million for this objective of Hungary, on the use of the remaining EUR 150 million later, the decision to extend the contract of credit.
The parties signed a contract on 50 million for innovations, what the budget used mainly for the draft innovations and research at the University of Debrecen.
During the talks the issue of the construction of the 4 to line of the underground.
The agreement was reached that by the time Hungary with the EU finalised the details of the financing of the underground, will deal with that if necessary or not to amend the original contract and how to do it.
According to János Veres, this will take place later in the first quarter of 2008.
Since 1990 the EIB financed in total 113 projects in Hungary worth 8.4 billion euros.
The interest of the appropriations are in line with the and the EIB offers a grace period of 8 years, without charge Commission to keep the credit available to the debtor.
Bulgaria, paradise property of the EU
It is admirable development of the property market Bulgarian - the attention of the whole of Europe is heading for this Balkan country before little mentioned.
What, where and those who buy in the market even cheaper EU, will rise quickly?
analysis of the division of Bulgarian re / Max.
The objective preferred to takeovers property in Eastern Europe is undoubtedly Bulgaria, with its cheap flats of ski slopes and the villa of the beaches.
The regions Montanosas of Bansko, Borovec, Pamprovo and Vitosa are the most favourite, whereas in the beaches Albena, the "golden coast," the "coast of the sun", the former Sozopol and Nesebar, but more and more people looking for buildings in the vicinity of Kavarna and Balchik.
According to analysts re / Max in Bulgaria sooner or later, also the central part of the country - as Veliko Tarnovo, Gabrovo, Elena, Triavna - and more and more people buy property in the area especially cheap.
Similarly can be attractive the capital Sofia, commercial spaces and offices promise a quick return on investment.
Bulgaria is in the best way to become one of the most commendable havens of golf of Europe, and could be a destination also highlighted during the other two stations, as well as the summer and winter.
Therefore, cautious investors are already making their purchases, for example in the vicinity of Bansko.
In the view of analysts, those who buy property in Bulgaria, are trying to change their lives and their way of life.
The majority of customers are English, but are also of France, Belgium, and increasingly Espana of Romania.
Also present promoters Maltese and Cypriot and traditionally there are many customers Russians on the beaches of the Black Sea and ski havens.
Customers foreigners can be classified into three groups - says Georgi Jankov, Director of regional re / Max in Bulgaria.
Those seeking to settle here buy property at a price between 50 and 100 thousand euros or old houses in poor condition between 5 and 15, 000 euros, to renew them then.
Require good communication and access, as well as for them is important proximity of a big city, shops and generally of a local doctor.
Constitute the second category purchasers of chalets (Bulgaria in December was included among the first 10 holiday destinations of Germans).
The third group are real estate investors who make their purchases in the hope of benefit in the medium or long term.
The price of property Capitalinos is in constant growth, since the demand is increasing.
Although in the European Union Bulgaria has home prices lower, in the last five years these suffered an annual increase of 21%
The increase in the price of property exceeds considerably wage growth.
Fodor and for the six hundred Hungarians
According to informed the Minister for the environment and Hidrología Gábor Fodor meetings at expert level be completed on Tuesday and Wednesday after the official opening negotiations will continue at ministerial level on the international climate regime post - 2012.
Experts and politicians from 192 countries of the world deliberate on the road map of Balí available on the efforts after the period of emission reduction, as set out in the Kyoto Protocol, valid until 2012.
At the present time are carried out lively discussions on the particularly among developing countries and the industrialised.
The United States has already indicated that for the time being does not want to negotiate on precise figures, although tends to reach an agreement that compared with the situation in 1990, until 2020 decline with 25 to 40% emissions of gases responsible for the greenhouse effect.
Another major theme of the conference is that if the industrialized countries, as well as reducing emissions, or are not prepared to provide assistance to countries in need.
An agreement was reached in addition offer on aid to developing countries.
The support fund, provided for in the Kyoto Protocol, will be led by a board of directors made up of 16 members, probably within the global fund for the environment of the UN (GEF) - writes the "Piac."
The six by hundreds of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, the environment minister and Hidrología Gábor Fodor supports the efforts of the EU to maintain its leading role in the global protection of the climate and promoting the signing of the new international agreement until 2009.
The Minister stated that the EU is committed to reduce by 2020, with regard to the 1990 level by 20% their emissions of gas, responsible for the greenhouse effect will be signed, regardless of whether or not the post - 2012 "and is ready to engage to reduce as high as 30%, when the other major developed regions of the world and developing countries in line with their responsibility and their skills.
Gábor Fodor pointed out that the countries that are signatories to the Kyoto Protocol of 1997 undertook to reduce 5.2%, within this the then 15 EU Member States committed themselves to meet an 8% reduction.
The commitment of Hungary is decreasing with 6% gas emissions responsible for the greenhouse effect with regard to the period between 1985 and 87, that our country will fulfil - Senala the press release of the Ministry of the environment.
Much is at stake in Balí, given that in two years we will have to sign the agreement international climate policy in the longer term, because if we do not, it is certain that its entry into force would continue after 2012. In this case the reduction commitments it made in the Kyoto Protocol would not be followed immediately by a new international system of reducing emissions, the need for which was perceived in its most recent report by the IPCC, Association international scientific UN dealing with climate change, which won the Nobel Prize for Peace.
Thus, the reduction of emissions would suffer a delay and could not prevent an increase of over 2 or C of the average temperature of the earth, According to scientists would have consequences unimaginable and irreversible.
The British army recruited in Youtube
units of the army in a British distributor of videos published recordings on actions filmed in Iraq and Afghanistan to popularise themselves.
First the British air force (RAD) was which took advantage of the services of Youtube: the special units displaced in Afghanistan since the March 2006 are burden videos on their actions against the Taliban - the BBC reported.
These recordings made with mini cameras riding on the helmets are monitored the body's general operations of Kandahar, then are sent to London to be loaded to the Internet.
The political message is inevitable
are already 139 recordings from air force soldiers who have been charged in this way to the Internet and its "channel" has been seen by more than 75 thousand people.
The British Defence Ministry was recorded in the spring of 2007 under the name of "defence" and published videos both of actions perpetrated in Iraq as in Afghanistan, while both the Ministry of the Community of Nations (British Commonwealth Office) as the multinational forces in Iraq (Mnfi) have their own channel Youtube.
Operation in Afghanistan
Originally the air force had loaded the videos with objectives of recruitment, but in the view of the Ministry of Defence also serve to present to the public the real objective of the presence of the British army abroad.
This kind of propaganda practically costs nothing compared to the TV spots conventional recruitment - told the BBC the expert on defence Gordon Mackenzie - on the other hand, inevitably have a political message, since in a specific way justify the raison d'être of the military action decided by the government.
The Americans prepared a videogame
The army is also concerned by the fact that, in addition to the recordings Recelosamente published and criticized, in the distributor are also videos fans, for example on the death of the soldiers: in the films of propaganda "official" a little hypocritical, officers speak a maximum of losses, however, without presenting the bloody part of the fighting.
In addition, the battlefields of Iraq and Afghanistan have borne the Internet already numerous videos enshrined in real operations, but the British army only recently is taking advantage of this opportunity.
The Americans used a slightly different for recruitment with the free Descargables video games of gunfire so-called America's army, where in the midst of a situation more or less real player can be directly instead of soldiers.
