The Czech Republic has the chance of getting 365 billion
The Ministers of the government of the Czech Republic signed yesterday with representatives of the European Commission a total of nine of the operational programmes that the Czech Republic can achieve 14 billion euros (roughly 365 billion Crowns).
This is half of the total sum that the Czech Republic can obtain from Brussels for the years 2007 to 2013.
Seven of operational programmes will be approximately 125 billion Crowns for the regions.
Czech companies will be able to obtain around 100 billion Crowns the programme of enterprise and innovation.
Most of the money will go to the transport, up to 150 billion.
The programme of transport is the largest of the operational programmes and represents up to 22% of the resources that the Czech Republic can achieve the Fund.
This money is increasing the budget of the State fund for transport infrastructure that next year will have the amount of 90.800 million kroner.
The programme of enterprise and innovation should serve to entrepreneurs and companies to obtain resources in innovation of business.
Companies should get funding for the acquisition of new technologies, for industrial research and for the implementation of organisational methods more effective.
With regard to the use of EU funds, the Czech Republic is among the Recien that less use them.
