600 not achieved thousand people to change their driving licence
Six hundred thousand drivers are spent the date and therefore not achieved to change their old card lead the validity of which expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can apply for change so that officials them time until the end of the year in issuing the new card.
However, the Ministry not concerned that after the new year on the roads are hundreds of thousands of drivers without the card valid.
According to traffic, the card have not changed mainly those who no longer want to drive.
While the people in announcing a rapid decline of the change of cards, the offices of the metropolis full of applications and the interest in the new card has increased.
The city estimated around 2 000 customers a day.
In queues is expected a half an hour.
In Prague have not yet been drawn by the new card around 140 000 drivers.
The issuing of a new card lasted twenty Dias.
However, it is possible to ask for the issuing of the card in a shorter term of five Dias.
But in that case the driver must pay 500 kroner.
Drivers who necessarily must change their card and do not achieve until the end of the year, but will be to the roads without the card applies to a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand kroner.
The police can settle the infringement with a reprimand.
If it was a breach administrative the fine will rise to EUR 2.5 kroner.
According to the information previous could receive a fine that person that it is not going nowhere.
Could presumably pay up to 30,000 Crowns.
The Ministry appealed to the offices to enter moderately fines of thousand kroner, at the most.
According to the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, fines of thousand kroner do not threaten anyone.
According to him, the driving licence is a document in which people can decide whether they want it or not.
It is not the identity card that every person must have valid.
People who do not want to lead should hand over the card lead.
Enough to bring it or send it by post certificate to the municipal offices.
At the end of the year no longer valid the cards issued during the years 1964 and 1993.
However, drivers should gradually be changing other types of driving licence.
People with the document between the years 1994 to 2000 have up to three years to change it.
The validity of the card that was issued between 2001 and 2004 ends in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka these are 2.6 million documents more.
