Perhaps, only to point out that in the aforementioned finance Hemingway there is a museum that for those who are lovers writer, must not fail to visit it.
The valley Viñales is the most scenic corner of Cuba to the west of the island.
Exuberant vegetation growing on land of rock.
Mogotes, Pilones of rock and rocks of high Escarpados in the Caidas of the valley, and in their Grutas is Aclimatan fertile land which are formed Roquedales that swept dense vegetation.
The valley is the place where it is grown, probably, higher quality tobacco in Cuba.
