Perhaps someone seems interesting that there is the Chilean part of the series, the more monstrous.
Trinidad
city of old pedigree that was founded not long after the Spanish Colonizaran the island.
Slavery and the sugar brought fame and wealth.
The wealth became beauty with constructions in the small town.
The architecture colonial Spanish, especially influenced by the settlers French arrived later, in four centuries little has changed.
Trinidad, between the sea and the Sierra of Escambray, is a place so (still in the 1950s of the last century there was that the road to join with the rest of the country.
Such isolation helped the stay out of the rest.
Nothing new was built, either, and so nothing was destroyed, for every person was happy to be where to live.
