Baracoa
small town in the Far West of Cuba, some consider it as the most beautiful of the island.
Surely that view is confirmed by the own way.
The two roads coming back from Guantanamo must go through ups and Quebradas mountains, how for a nature that hardly knows the action of man.
This place Eastern Cuba has been included as a world heritage by UNESCO intact thanks to their nature.
There are doing the best chocolate, in his church have the Cross of Columbus (it is actually a cross that came 100 years later of the landing) and from the hill, where was the castle and that there is now a hotel with the same name, you can see the mountains and including the best known, the anvil.
