The state debt of the Czech Republic grew at the end of September to 842.700 million kroner.
In nine months of this year increased by 40.200 million kroner.
However, since June fell 13.400 million kroner.
So today, the Ministry of Economy confirmed their data on the debt of the state of the beginning of October.
For every Czech debt is up to $84 kroner.
