But I do not see such a change, "he added.
The doubt is growing
The debt of the State creates debts in the central government and, above all, arises from the accumulation of the deficit of the state budget.
The debt of the State is paid through Treasury bonds, obligations of the state, or for example loans from the European Investment Bank.
The internal debt of the State rose this year of 38.5 million to 719.400 million kroner.
The foreign debt by now has grown 1.7 million kroner to 123.300 million kroner.
The so-called debt of the State at the end of September negotiable contained 803.300 million kroner Z since June was reduced in 13.700 million kroner.
The expiry half of the state debt increased by 6.5 years.
"The total debt year on year from the first to the third quarter Creción a 13% what is enormous given as it does the economy.
It is interesting that growth is generated above all of the obligations where there is a growth of 20%.
It is bad enough that the debt is growing but on the other hand, shows that it is going to negotiate until there is a pension reform "commented Pikora.
Better than expected
The strategy of payments and debt management of the state for the year 2007 is extracted that the government planned this year paid 159.200 million kroner.
At the beginning of December, the Ministry diminished the plan in 152.800 million kroner thanks to the improvement of the development of the state budget.
The amount is made up, in particular, the deficit of the state budget this year will be of 76 million kroner in than those provided 91.300 million kroner.
The rest is made up of maximum resources planned for the Agency Czech consolidation with 13.300 million kroner, the reserve of 10 billion kroner for the payment of pensions, 43 billion Crowns to finance the obligations of the state and 1.8 million kroner in payments of loans from the European Investment Bank.
Likened today in front of a court to Khartoum for having given a name to a bear of cute
Professor British judged in Sudan to insult to Islam has been sentenced on Thursday afternoon by a court in Khartoum to 15 days in prison and expulsion, indicated his lawyer.
The British was accused of having left pupils of 6 to 7 years to give the name of Mahomet to a bear of when any representation of the prophet of Islam is illegal.
It was Pasible of a death lashes.
This grand British school age 54 years according to the high school of Khartoum in Sudan, was arrested on Sunday at home and charged of attack on Islam and of sedition, under Article 125 of the penal code Sudanese, as a result of several complaints from parents of pupils in the Sudanese Ministry of Education.
The story goes back to September, when the teacher calls on their pupils, of 6/7 years of age, choose a name for the bear of class.
"Eight names out of the mouths of children, such as Hassan, Abdullah and Mohammed", the director of the school Robert Boulos.
Finally, after a vote in class, 20 children of every 23 have Elegigo to Mohamed as behalf preferred.
Mohamed is of course the name of the Prophet Muslim, but above all a name very common in Sudan.
Then the children have done a paper to the class with the photo of the bear with the following legend "my name is Mohamed."
The bear him - there had been no label with the name, but the problem is simply the representation of the Prophet regarded as an insult to Islam.
One of the fellow Muslims Gillian, Professor in the same school in Sudan, stated that the well known and that would never have done something that could be insulting to a religious faith, "I am sorry that only has asked children to vote for a name," according to him it is only of an "honest mistake".
Opinion divided by many pupils of the grand school that described as "very attentive to their pupils" and "ever talks about religion in class.".
Let us remember that the name Mohamed is also the second name more given in Great Britain, is written in English with 14 different ways.
The name often Elegigo by the families Muslim is a way of honouring the Prophet (often given to the first child of a family).
But what are the rules concerning the use of the name?
For example can we give it to a plaything?
This is of course a matter of interpretation.
On Wednesday have not reached an agreement on the future status of the province, during the last session of negotiations in Vienna.
In the end, the failure.
The Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo have come to an end on Wednesday morning to Baden, Austria, in a sixth and last session of discussions without having been able to overcome their differences about the future status of the separatist province.
"It is regrettable that the parties have not been able to reach agreement on the Statute," said the mediator European Wolfgang Ischinger, at a press conference in Vienna.
Stressing that peace in the region was "at stake", its American counterpart, frank Wisner, urged Belgrade and Pristina to respect its efforts to preserve peace and dialogue beyond the end of the negotiations.
"We do not anticipate violence but for now entering a very difficult period," he added, pointing out that "obvious tensions exist."
So mediation on 10 December
The mediators of the troika, which brings together the European Union, the United States and Russia, Iran one last time on Monday in Serbia and Kosovo.
The future of the province populated 90% of Albanians could become more clear when Ischinger, Wisner and the Russian mediator Alexander Botsane-khartchenko returned its relationship to the Security Council of the United Nations, between now and December 10.
The discussions in Baden, near Vienna, were the sixth and final session of negotiations since the troika has been responsible for a new mediation by the UN, the last August.
Americans and Europeans see their mediation will be completed on 10 December.
The Russians, who have already blocked in the Security Council the granting of independence in Kosovo, insisting them in a persecution of the negotiations beyond this deadline.
"Russia was and remains committed in favour of a negotiated solution, a compromise," he said Botsane-khartchenko.
What unilateral declaration of independence?
After eight years of UN administration of Kosovo, the Western believe that the independence under supervision of the European Union is the only viable solution.
Pristina is ready to proclaim it unilaterally if the Security Council does not resolve in his favour.
Belgrade insists on autonomy Acrecida.
"Unfortunately, no agreement has been found," announced the President of the autonomous authority of Kosovo, Fatmir Sejdiu, in the hotel where they were being held since Monday these "negotiations of the last chance."
Hashim Thaci, a former Commander of the rebellion in Kosovo and future Prime Minister of the province, has taken part of their everything.
But he went on to say that the level of autonomy presented by Belgrade "belonged to a past that has led to murder and deportations."
"domino effect"
The Serbian President Boris Tadic has Considerato for its part that a compromise was always feasible, warning the Albanian majority in Kosovo against the consequences of a unilateral proclamation of the independence of the province.
Belgrade says particularly fear a "domino effect" in a region still weakened by the independence wars of the 1990's.
"For Serbia, he said, this does not mean that a compromise impossible."
On Tuesday, the delegation Serbia had insisted that any decision to belong exclusively to the Security Council, in which its ally Russian has a right of veto.
"The Parliament of Kosovo will have the final say"
"only a solution within the Security Council is acceptable to Serbia", had declared the Serbian Prime Minister, Vojislav Kostunica.
"These negotiations have lasted two years.
Must stop as have started: in the Security Council. "
Journalists, Fatmir Sedjiu had responded that "the Parliament of Kosovo will have the last word on the statute", adding that any unilateral declaration of independence on the part of the Albanians would be "in consultation" with the West.
Bush begins an agreement between Israelis and Palestinians
President George Bush announced, during the size of the international peace conference assembled by himself on Tuesday in Annapolis, Maryland, that the Israelis and the Palestinians had finally reached agreement on a joint declaration.
Specified that Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Olmert and Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas had agreed to enter into negotiations immediately in view of finding a definitive regulation of the old 60 years between the two peoples.
In the presence of both men, Bush promised that we would do everything to help them to conclude a "Peace Treaty" before the end of 2008.
In the meantime, the Palestinians must dismantle "terrorist infrastructure" and Israel must stop its activities of colonisation, Bush said, recalling both sides to their obligations on the roadmap for peace that accepted in 2003.
The head of the White House stressed that the negotiations between Israel and the Palestinian authority led by Abbas attempt "to conclude a peace agreement which would solve all the outstanding issues, without exception, including the core issues."
This designation Recubre the three main point between Israelis and Palestinians: the future borders of Palestine, the status of Jerusalem and the fate of Arab refugees driven from their homes during the conflict in 1948.
Taking the floor after the American President, Abbas insisted that the negotiations to come are "global and Aprofundizadas" and refer in all aspects of a regulation, citing "Jerusalem, refugees, borders, settlements, water, security, among other things."
Subendo on his return in the gallery, Olmert undertook to what the future negotiations should be "direct and continuous" and "make an effort to conclude them in the course of the year 2008."
Bush set at the end of the year 2008 the end of the implementation of his "vision of two states" Palestinian and Israeli coexist.
Saudi Arabia revealed that it had made a commitment in this respect of Bush before deciding to participate in the Conference.
Arabia, whose participation to Annapolis is a success for Washington, is at the beginning of a level, saddled by all the Arab countries, which proposes peace to Israel in exchange for its withdrawal from all the occupied Arab territories during the 1967 war, including East Jerusalem.
Annapolis marks "a point of confrontation in the history of the Middle East, in particular because it attacks the roots of the conflict and its priorities", estimated Prince Saoud in his newspaper interview with Arab capitals Saudis.
