who happen to Poutine to the Presidency?
The official newspaper published yesterday the date of the first round of the presidential election, on 2 March 2008; the candidates have until 23 December to know.
Elected in 2000 and elected again in 2004, Vladimir Putin can not seek the third term in a row.
Then no successor emerges.
What role will play Poutine after March?
What Prime Minister?
Does head of the parliamentary majority and the very powerful United Russia party that Elegería the government and the President?
Whatever, to the legislative elections and the presidential power, outgoing triumph.
It is a tradition.
"The Russians kept the mentality of homo Sovieticus, do not feel masters of their own destiny", estimated the sociologist Goudkov, Director of the Centre independent Levada.
The historian Nikolaï Kopossov, of the State University of St. Petersburg, goes back further: civil society be delayed in this country Cristianizado five centuries after Europe; the famous spirit of the Community delayed the formation of individualism.
After the liberal reforms of the 1990s, "Poutine restored the model of a paternalistic State, fully accepted by the population as this new paternalism has not been followed by terrorism, but by a true confession economic", estimated Maria Lipman, of the Carnegie Foundation.
Today the Russians "they give up on their own will on the personal responsibility" of those who briefly had shown after the outbreak of the USSR.
"What reflect?"
The phenomenon affects all sections of society, including the world affairs.
And the elite administrative intends to preserve the status quo: 65 governors (of each 85 heads of Russian regions) run the lists of the local United Russia.
The new freedoms imported from the West are often Sinónimas of chaos, as in the 1990s.
The opinion prefers stability.
On behalf of the Russians will not be voting either by extremists.
Conclusion of Tamara Tcherednitchenko, a professor of age of 54 years: "Why should they reflect?
What those in power are not too bad, why change them? "
A memory heavy
After more than 60 years of confidentiality, archives Nazis of bad Arolsen, which describe the fates of 17.5 million victims of Hitler's regime, are in free access.
The 47 million documents archives, stored on 27 km of Estanterias to bad Arolsen (Hesse), they were not so much Consultables only an end "humanitarian" that is individually and, at the request of a former victim or their eligible parties.
The 11 States responsible for its management - such as Germany, France, Israel and the United States - agreed in May 2006 for the Abrírlos seekers and historians.
As the process of ratification of this agreement by all the countries is over, the size is effective from yesterday.
Sensitive information
The access of historians to bad Arolsen enable searches "particularly on the movement of Prisonieros, the population of the camps and the state of health of workers forced", explains challenge Meistern, the director of these archives administered by the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC).
Until recently, a number of States, such as Germany, were opposed to the size of these documents to the public nominative, because of the sensitivity of certain information.
As well as the alleged homosexuality or the handicap of certain mental victims of the deportation.
The records of the concentration camps or the arrest warrants set by the Gestapo had been gathered after war in an end practical: find the fellow countrymen deported or under compulsory at work and, possibly, give them a test of their detention, in order to pave the way for its compensation.
Even today in bad Arolsen, more than 300 employees permanent deal tens of thousands of petitions individual.
However, for some of the scientific community, access to bad Arolsen is of limited interest.
"There is nothing fundamentally new that we should wait for these documents," had declared in 2006 Professor Wolfgang Benz, Director of the Centre for Busqueda on Anti-Semitism in the Technische Universität Berlin.
