Black also showed their concerns that the Scottish NHS has no idea of the exact amount of foreign staff available.
However, the report pointed out that other controls are carried out properly by means of a sample of five health authorities.
The auditor general Chequeó the amount of foreign staff employed outside the European economic area, as a result of the attacks on the Glasgow airport.
