Venus: twin brother of the earth.
Despite its atmosphere is not suitable for life, Venus is the planet more like the earth, which so far had not been raised. The European probe "Venus" discovered rays in the atmosphere and Remolinos in the Poles, the same people who are also in winter on earth.
For the past three decades, the researchers had the suspicion that there may be rays in Venus.
But now the European probe has brought new evidence, discovered electromagnetic waves on the edge of the atmosphere. In the rays Venus Cayen of heights of 54 kilometres of a cloud and behind another, account Russell of the University of California at Los Angeles to the scientific journal "nature."
According to the famous model of the origin of life of Urey-miller, the rays caused life on earth: the storms could have led to reactions in the ocean, for its part, had led to the amino acids that are the building blocks of life.
In Venus is not the case: if one day there were living there, it would have to be in one of the first states of development ", explains be Solomon of the Carnegie institution of Washington.
Today, on the surface of Venus life: there can be no pressure air is almost 100 times greater than on earth and the surface temperatures reign of 500° C, in such a way that can be achieved temperatures below zero.
"Possibly, Venus is a twin" diabolical "of the land, but it is still a twin," said Russell.
The main objective of the mission "Venus" is to respond to the question as to why Venus, so similar to the land for its size, and has had a development so different.
Since the 1990s as there was no specific missions, only for research on this planet, the launch of "Venus-express" in November 2005 was a very important step for research of Venus.
Recent research results which will be presented in many articles of "nature", according to researchers, underscore not only the uniqueness of Venus in the solar system.
"This Desmuestra also that planets neighbours have more common characteristics to the land from which assumed," informs the ESA.
Despite the already known stormy winds in the North Pole, researchers found in the region polar South also a Vórtice made up of the clouds that revolves faster.
This phenomenon is reminiscent of the flow of wind at a high layers atmospheric land of the Poles, according to a team of researchers described by Giuseppe Piccioni of the Italian Institute of special and physical space.
The second planet of the solar system has the mass almost equal to that land and with its Equatorial diameter of 12 000 kilometres is almost as big.
This planet also known as star Alba or star evening orbit around the sun almost 225 days.
But its period of rotation is slower: a day when Venus is equivalent to 243 days on earth.
Although Venus with their surface temperatures 460 degrees and with its atmospheric pressure of 92 bars not resembles much to the land, scientists assume that both planets were formed under the same conditions.
In the two planets had been patchwork water on earth stayed in the oceans, but in Venus in the universe.
While in the earth carbon dioxide had become stones carbon, in Venus form the majority of the atmosphere.
